Program: Outlook
Title: 07/06/2012
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00sqwbv
Last Broadcast Date: Fri 8 Jun 2012
Extraordinary personal stories from around the world. Today, Youssef Al Kilani who led Colonel Gaddafi's son Saif al-Islam to his captors - and lost everything because of the enemies he has made as a result. Also, burying the typewriter - a childhood under surveillance in Ceausescu's Romania.